==Trivia==
[[File:Gladiator Poster.PNG|thumb|250px|The poster of a Gladiator on the wall is based on the cover of [[w:c:marvel:Daredevil Vol 1 226|''Daredevil'' Vol 1 #226]]]]
*In the comics, Melvin Potter is known as '''Gladiator''' and one of [[Daredevil]]'s first enemies, eventually becoming his ally.
**The symbol that Potter uses on his costume in the comics can be seen in his [[Melvin Potter's Workshop|workshop]] and on his personal body armor.
*Potter drinks {{WPS|Yoo-hoo}}{{Ref|DD111}} and he likes asopao, a Hispanic stew.{{Ref|DD307}}

==Behind the Scenes==
*According to [[Erik Oleson]], Potter's arc in the cancelled fourth season of ''[[Daredevil (TV series)|Daredevil]]'' would have led to him assuming his identity as ''Gladiator'' from the comics.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2J0Jr_OmDg8 A Conversation with Daredevil Showrunners Erik Oleson and Steven DeKnight]</ref>
*[[Anthony Mecca]] was a stunt double for [[Matt Gerald]] in the role of Melvin Potter.

